ippers have lived in Bengal/Assam/T=\r\nripura/Odisha. This has caused&nbsp;the notion of Kali to get ingrained in =\r\nthe very culture. Even sufis in Bengal worship Kaali. But the key is to acc=\r\nept Her and love Her, AS SHE IS! Which means, say if you find the garland o=\r\nf skulls on her neck and the skull in her hand disturbing, or if you find t=\r\nhe blood-dripping from the freshly cut head in Her hand difficult to relate=\r\n to, you cannot cannot replace&nbsp;those from her iconography and expect t=\r\no get clear results from your worship. Love Her the way She is, in her fero=\r\ncity and wildness and beauty. When you do that, you&#39;re game.&nbsp;Yes She&n=\r\nbsp;can be dreadful, but that is how She is loved by her devotees, without =\r\ntrying to modify Her innate nature and characteristics. Relate to Her as Ma=\r\n, but don&#39;t ask Her\n to remove the skulls. &lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;Th=\r\ne&nbsp;traditional&nbsp;idea, which I believe to be correct,&nbsp;is to wor=\r\nship the form in the way it is and love and relate to it in all its attribu=\r\ntes. I know a certain person who used to&nbsp;worship a very fierce form of=\r\n Devi but mentally was&nbsp;unable to relate to that form. She was adviced =\r\nby her guru to do so, who used to worship that fierce form himself. When I =\r\nasked her what does she feel about the deity, she said I mentally think of =\r\nHer of Gouri but perform the ritual for the fierce form&nbsp;as my Guru ask=\r\ned me to. I of course had no business interfering in the relationship betwe=\r\nen a Guru and his disciple and so kept my mouth shut, but personally I was =\r\nextremely skeptical of this approach. When you can&#39;t even love&nbsp;the for=\r\nm you are worshipping, then what kind of worship is that? Later she met ano=\r\nther individual who acted as a mentor and gave her a mantra of a much milde=\r\nr form of God. Today&nbsp;the lady spends\n nearly&nbsp;8 hours every day im=\r\nmersed in the worship of that milder&nbsp;form. Her spiritual life leap-fro=\r\ngged once she started worshipping the milder form of God. Thats why the Tan=\r\ntras stress so heavily on the importance of&nbsp;correct form for each indi=\r\nvidual. &lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;It is not my =\r\ncontention that worshipping an urga deity is difficult or simple compared t=\r\no worshipping a milder form. Both are difficult and to succeed in any worsh=\r\nip&nbsp;a combination of various factors must fall in place. It&#39;s like tryi=\r\nng to judge, which among Rugby and Table-tennis, is a more difficult game. =\r\nSome like one, some like the other, but you cannot pass a judgement about w=\r\nhich is more dificult. &lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;-Take Care&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;=\r\n&nbsp; Rajarshi&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div style=3D&quot;FONT-FAMILY:times=\r\n new roman, new york, times, serif;FONT-SIZE:12pt;&quot;&gt;\n&lt;div style=3D&quot;FONT-FAM=\r\nILY:times new roman, new york, times, serif;FONT-SIZE:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=3D&quot;=\r\nArial&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;\n&lt;div style=3D&quot;BORDER-BOTTOM:#ccc 1px solid;BORDER-LEFT:#=\r\nccc 1px solid;HEIGHT:0px;FONT-SIZE:0px;BORDER-TOP:#ccc 1px solid;BORDER-RIG=\r\nHT:#ccc 1px solid;&quot; class=3D&quot;yiv22887326hr&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;FONT-WE=\r\nIGHT:bold;&quot;&gt;From:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Srikanth &lt;srikanthnetworked@...&gt;&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;FONT-WEIGHT:bold;&quot;&gt;To:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; vedic-wisdom@yahoogro=\r\nups.com &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;FONT-WEIGHT:bold;&quot;&gt;Sent:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Wednesday=\r\n, 21 December 2011 8:09 PM&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;FONT-WEIGHT:bold;&quot;&gt;Subject:=\r\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Re: [vedic-wisdom] Re: Maha